Package gradescope

Class Trader

  • java.lang.Object
    • gradescope.Trader
  • public class Trader
extends Object
    Represents a trader on the market who can buy/sell products. Each trader has a unique string id, a balance (can be negative), and an inventory of products with associated amounts.

      • importProduct

        public double importProduct​(String product,
                            double amount)
        Imports product into the trader's inventory. If the product is null or the amount is less than or equal to zero, return -1.0.
        Parameters:
        product - The product to import.
        amount - The amount to import.
        Returns:
        The amount of the product the trader now has in their inventory.

      • exportProduct

        public double exportProduct​(String product,
                            double amount)
        Exports product out of the trader's inventory. If the product is null or the amount is less than or equal to zero, return -1.0. If the trader does not have the product, or does not have enough of the product, do nothing and return -1.0.
        Parameters:
        product - The product to export.
        amount - The amount to export.
        Returns:
        The amount of the product the trader now has in their inventory.

      • getAmountStored

        public double getAmountStored​(String product)
        Returns the amount of the given product the trader has in their inventory. If the product is null, return -1.0.
        Parameters:
        product - The product to be compared with.
        Returns:
        The amount of the given product in the inventory.

      • adjustBalance

        public double adjustBalance​(double change)

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Returns a string representation of the trader. Format: ID: $BALANCE {PROD1: AMOUNT1, PROD2: AMOUNT2, ...., PRODN: AMOUNTN}
        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
        Returns:

      • writeTraders

        public static void writeTraders​(List<Trader> traders,
                                String path)
        Writes the list of traders to file in ASCII encoding. For every trader in the provided list, write the String representation on a new line in the given file. If either argument is invalid, do nothing.
        Parameters:
        traders - The list of traders to write.
        path - The file path.

      • writeTradersBinary

        public static void writeTradersBinary​(List<Trader> traders,
                                      String path)
        Writes the list of traders to file in binary encoding. For every trader in the provided list, write the String representation, followed by the Unit Separator byte. If either argument is invalid, do nothing.
        Parameters:
        traders - The list of traders to write.
        path - The file path.
